The DR.OH - Pocket General Hospital app uses the information we collect about you for the following general purposes:
register and manage Your account, including allowing You to access and use our website;
communicating with You in general, including providing information about DR.OH - Pocket General Hospital;
answer frequently asked questions;
evaluate interest in and improve our programs and Websites;
inform you of the programs and plans of advocacy campaigns;
receive information from you, including through surveys about volunteer programs;
resolve disputes or troubleshoot problems;
prevent potentially illegal or prohibited activities from occurring;
enforce our Terms of Use and other purposes notified to You at the time of collection;
announce the results of advocacy programs as well as the use of those assets in the program.
If you have registered as a member we will email you to the email address you provided to us.
Units of the Fund and our affiliates. We may share your personal information within DR.OH Pocket General Hospital. This sharing allows us to provide you with information about plans and advocacy programs that may be of interest to you.
